# Container SAST baseline — epic #448 / TRK-311 (Layer 1).
#
# This repo root is the BUILD CONTEXT for da-portal and tenant-api
# (component-docker-build.yaml uses `context: .` for both). Docker reads
# .dockerignore from the context root, so this file governs what those two
# image builds receive. Keeping .git history, CI/test/script/doc trees,
# secrets and logs out of the context shrinks the upload and prevents
# secret/.env leakage into images.
#
# Dir exclusions are ANCHORED (leading /) to the repo root so same-named
# subdirs under copied source (e.g. components/**/tests/) are not pruned.
# *.md / *.log / .env* are intentionally unanchored — drop them at any depth.
/.git/
/.github/
/scripts/
/tests/
/docs/
*.md
*.log
.env*

# Re-include the static assets da-portal's Dockerfile COPYs from the repo-root
# context. Without these the da-portal image build fails ("not found") because
# the /docs/ exclusion above would prune them from the context.
#
# NOTE: REQUIRES BuildKit. This exclude-then-re-include (`/docs/` then
# `!/docs/interactive/`) works under BuildKit (CI uses docker/setup-buildx;
# `make pre-tag` uses buildx; Docker 23+ defaults to BuildKit). The LEGACY
# builder (`DOCKER_BUILDKIT=0`) abandons an excluded dir and IGNORES the
# re-include → a local `docker build -f components/da-portal/Dockerfile .`
# fails with "docs/interactive: not found". Fix on such hosts: enable
# BuildKit (`DOCKER_BUILDKIT=1` / `docker buildx build`).
!/docs/interactive/
!/docs/assets/
!/docs/.nojekyll
